{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"It can be a very complicated thing, the ocean."},{"time":3000,"text":"And it can be a very complicated thing, what human health is."},{"time":6000,"text":"And bringing those two together might seem a very daunting task,"},{"time":9000,"text":"but what I'm going to try to say is that"},{"time":11000,"text":"even in that complexity,"},{"time":13000,"text":"there's some simple themes that I think,"},{"time":15000,"text":"if we understand, we can really move forward."},{"time":18000,"text":"And those simple themes aren't really"},{"time":20000,"text":"themes about the complex science of what's going on,"},{"time":22000,"text":"but things that we all pretty well know."},{"time":24000,"text":"And I'm going to start with this one:"},{"time":26000,"text":"If momma ain't happy, ain't nobody happy."},{"time":29000,"text":"We know that, right? We've experienced that."},{"time":32000,"text":"And if we just take that"},{"time":34000,"text":"and we build from there,"},{"time":36000,"text":"then we can go to the next step,"},{"time":38000,"text":"which is that if the ocean ain't happy,"},{"time":41000,"text":"ain't nobody happy."},{"time":43000,"text":"That's the theme of my talk."},{"time":45000,"text":"And we're making the ocean pretty unhappy in a lot of different ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"This is a shot of Cannery Row in 1932."},{"time":51000,"text":"Cannery Row, at the time,"},{"time":53000,"text":"had the biggest industrial"},{"time":55000,"text":"canning operation on the west coast."},{"time":57000,"text":"We piled enormous amounts of pollution"},{"time":60000,"text":"into the air and into the water."},{"time":62000,"text":"Rolf Bolin, who was a professor"},{"time":64000,"text":"at the Hopkin's Marine Station where I work,"},{"time":66000,"text":"wrote in the 1940s that"},{"time":68000,"text":"\"The fumes from the scum floating on the inlets of the bay"},{"time":71000,"text":"were so bad they turned"},{"time":73000,"text":"lead-based paints black.\""},{"time":75000,"text":"People working in these canneries"},{"time":77000,"text":"could barely stay there all day because of the smell,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but you know what they came out saying?"},{"time":82000,"text":"They say, \"You know what you smell?"},{"time":84000,"text":"You smell money.\""},{"time":86000,"text":"That pollution was money to that community,"},{"time":89000,"text":"and those people dealt with the pollution"},{"time":91000,"text":"and absorbed it into their skin and into their bodies"},{"time":94000,"text":"because they needed the money."},{"time":96000,"text":"We made the ocean unhappy; we made people very unhappy,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and we made them unhealthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"The connection between ocean health and human health"},{"time":104000,"text":"is actually based upon another couple simple adages,"},{"time":107000,"text":"and I want to call that"},{"time":109000,"text":"\"pinch a minnow, hurt a whale.\""},{"time":111000,"text":"The pyramid of ocean life ..."},{"time":113000,"text":"Now, when an ecologist looks at the ocean -- I have to tell you --"},{"time":116000,"text":"we look at the ocean in a very different way,"},{"time":118000,"text":"and we see different things than when a regular person looks at the ocean"},{"time":121000,"text":"because when an ecologist looks at the ocean,"},{"time":123000,"text":"we see all those interconnections."},{"time":125000,"text":"We see the base of the food chain,"},{"time":127000,"text":"the plankton, the small things,"},{"time":129000,"text":"and we see how those animals"},{"time":131000,"text":"are food to animals in the middle of the pyramid,"},{"time":134000,"text":"and on so up this diagram."},{"time":138000,"text":"And that flow, that flow of life,"},{"time":140000,"text":"from the very base up to the very top,"},{"time":142000,"text":"is the flow that ecologists see."},{"time":144000,"text":"And that's what we're trying to preserve"},{"time":146000,"text":"when we say, \"Save the ocean. Heal the ocean.\""},{"time":149000,"text":"It's that pyramid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"Now why does that matter for human health?"},{"time":154000,"text":"Because when we jam things in the bottom"},{"time":156000,"text":"of that pyramid that shouldn't be there,"},{"time":158000,"text":"some very frightening things happen."},{"time":161000,"text":"Pollutants, some pollutants have been created by us:"},{"time":164000,"text":"molecules like PCBs"},{"time":166000,"text":"that can't be broken down by our bodies."},{"time":168000,"text":"And they go in the base of that pyramid,"},{"time":170000,"text":"and they drift up; they're passed up that way,"},{"time":173000,"text":"on to predators and on to the top predators,"},{"time":175000,"text":"and in so doing,"},{"time":177000,"text":"they accumulate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Now, to bring that home, I thought I'd invent a little game."},{"time":181000,"text":"We don't really have to play it; we can just think about it here."},{"time":183000,"text":"It's the Styrofoam and chocolate game."},{"time":185000,"text":"Imagine that when we got on this boat,"},{"time":188000,"text":"we were all given"},{"time":190000,"text":"two Styrofoam peanuts."},{"time":192000,"text":"Can't do much with them: Put them in your pocket."},{"time":194000,"text":"Suppose the rules are: every time you offer somebody a drink,"},{"time":197000,"text":"you give them the drink,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and you give them your Styrofoam peanuts too."},{"time":201000,"text":"What'll happen is that the Styrofoam peanuts"},{"time":203000,"text":"will start moving through our society here,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and they will accumulate in"},{"time":207000,"text":"the drunkest, stingiest people."},{"time":209000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":214000,"text":"There's no mechanism in this game"},{"time":216000,"text":"for them to go anywhere but into"},{"time":218000,"text":"a bigger and bigger pile"},{"time":220000,"text":"of indigestible Styrofoam peanuts."},{"time":222000,"text":"And that's exactly what happens with PDBs"},{"time":224000,"text":"in this food pyramid:"},{"time":226000,"text":"They accumulate into the top of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"Now suppose, instead of Styrofoam peanuts,"},{"time":231000,"text":"we take these lovely little chocolates that we get"},{"time":233000,"text":"and we had those instead."},{"time":235000,"text":"Well, some of us would be eating those chocolates"},{"time":237000,"text":"instead of passing them around,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and instead of accumulating,"},{"time":241000,"text":"they will just pass into our group here"},{"time":244000,"text":"and not accumulate in any one group"},{"time":246000,"text":"because they're absorbed by us."},{"time":248000,"text":"And that's the difference between a PCB"},{"time":250000,"text":"and, say, something natural like an omega-3,"},{"time":252000,"text":"something we want out of the marine food chain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"PCBs accumulate."},{"time":258000,"text":"We have great examples of that, unfortunately."},{"time":260000,"text":"PCBs accumulate in dolphins"},{"time":262000,"text":"in Sarasota Bay, in Texas, in North Carolina."},{"time":265000,"text":"They get into the food chain."},{"time":267000,"text":"The dolphins eat the fish"},{"time":269000,"text":"that have PCBs from the plankton,"},{"time":271000,"text":"and those PCBs, being fat-soluble,"},{"time":274000,"text":"accumulate in these dolphins."},{"time":276000,"text":"Now, a dolphin,"},{"time":278000,"text":"mother dolphin, any dolphin --"},{"time":280000,"text":"there's only one way"},{"time":282000,"text":"that a PCB can get out of a dolphin."},{"time":284000,"text":"And what's that?"},{"time":286000,"text":"In mother's milk."},{"time":288000,"text":"Here's a diagram of the PCB load"},{"time":290000,"text":"of dolphins in Sarasota Bay."},{"time":292000,"text":"Adult males: a huge load."},{"time":294000,"text":"Juveniles: a huge load."},{"time":296000,"text":"Females after their first calf is already weaned:"},{"time":298000,"text":"a lower load."},{"time":300000,"text":"Those females, they're not trying to."},{"time":302000,"text":"Those females are passing the PCBs"},{"time":304000,"text":"in the fat of their own mother's milk"},{"time":307000,"text":"into their offspring,"},{"time":309000,"text":"and their offspring don't survive."},{"time":312000,"text":"The death rate in these dolphins,"},{"time":314000,"text":"for the first calf born of every female dolphin,"},{"time":316000,"text":"is 60 to 80 percent."},{"time":318000,"text":"These mothers pump their first offspring"},{"time":321000,"text":"full of this pollutant,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and most of them die."},{"time":325000,"text":"Now, the mother then can go and reproduce,"},{"time":327000,"text":"but what a terrible price to pay"},{"time":329000,"text":"for the accumulation of this pollutant"},{"time":331000,"text":"in these animals --"},{"time":333000,"text":"the death of the first-born calf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"There's another top predator in the ocean, it turns out."},{"time":339000,"text":"That top predator, of course, is us."},{"time":341000,"text":"And we also are eating meat"},{"time":343000,"text":"that comes from some of these same places."},{"time":345000,"text":"This is whale meat"},{"time":347000,"text":"that I photographed in a grocery store in Tokyo --"},{"time":349000,"text":"or is it?"},{"time":351000,"text":"In fact, what we did a few years ago"},{"time":353000,"text":"was learn how to smuggle"},{"time":355000,"text":"a molecular biology lab into Tokyo"},{"time":357000,"text":"and use it to genetically test the DNA"},{"time":360000,"text":"out of whale meat samples"},{"time":362000,"text":"and identify what they really were."},{"time":364000,"text":"And some of those whale meat samples were whale meat."},{"time":366000,"text":"Some of them were illegal whale meat, by the way."},{"time":368000,"text":"That's another story."},{"time":370000,"text":"But some of them were not whale meat at all."},{"time":372000,"text":"Even though they were labeled whale meat, they were dolphin meat."},{"time":375000,"text":"Some of them were dolphin liver. Some of them were dolphin blubber."},{"time":378000,"text":"And those dolphin parts"},{"time":380000,"text":"had a huge load of PCBs,"},{"time":382000,"text":"dioxins and heavy metals."},{"time":385000,"text":"And that huge load was passing into the people"},{"time":387000,"text":"that ate this meat."},{"time":389000,"text":"It turns out that a lot of dolphins"},{"time":391000,"text":"are being sold as meat"},{"time":393000,"text":"in the whale meat market around the world."},{"time":395000,"text":"That's a tragedy for those populations,"},{"time":397000,"text":"but it's also a tragedy"},{"time":399000,"text":"for the people eating them"},{"time":401000,"text":"because they don't know that that's toxic meat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"We had these data a few years ago."},{"time":407000,"text":"I remember sitting at my desk"},{"time":409000,"text":"being about the only person in the world"},{"time":411000,"text":"who knew that whale meat being sold in these markets"},{"time":414000,"text":"was really dolphin meat, and it was toxic."},{"time":417000,"text":"It had two-to-three-to-400 times the toxic loads"},{"time":420000,"text":"ever allowed by the EPA."},{"time":422000,"text":"And I remember there sitting at my desk thinking,"},{"time":425000,"text":"\"Well, I know this. This is a great scientific discovery,\""},{"time":428000,"text":"but it was so awful."},{"time":430000,"text":"And for the very first time in my scientific career,"},{"time":432000,"text":"I broke scientific protocol,"},{"time":434000,"text":"which is that you take the data and publish them in scientific journals"},{"time":437000,"text":"and then begin to talk about them."},{"time":439000,"text":"We sent a very polite letter"},{"time":441000,"text":"to the Minister of Health in Japan"},{"time":444000,"text":"and simply pointed out that"},{"time":447000,"text":"this is an intolerable situation, not for us,"},{"time":449000,"text":"but for the people of Japan"},{"time":451000,"text":"because mothers who may be breastfeeding,"},{"time":454000,"text":"who may have young children,"},{"time":456000,"text":"would be buying something that they thought was healthy,"},{"time":459000,"text":"but it was really toxic."},{"time":461000,"text":"That led to a whole series of other campaigns in Japan,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and I'm really proud to say that at this point,"},{"time":467000,"text":"it's very difficult to buy anything in Japan"},{"time":470000,"text":"that's labeled incorrectly,"},{"time":472000,"text":"even though they're still selling whale meat,"},{"time":474000,"text":"which I believe they shouldn't."},{"time":476000,"text":"But at least it's labeled correctly,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and you're no longer going to be buying"},{"time":480000,"text":"toxic dolphin meat instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483000,"text":"It isn't just there that this happens,"},{"time":486000,"text":"but in a natural diet of some communities"},{"time":488000,"text":"in the Canadian arctic and in the United States"},{"time":490000,"text":"and in the European arctic,"},{"time":492000,"text":"a natural diet of seals and whales"},{"time":495000,"text":"leads to an accumulation of PCBs"},{"time":497000,"text":"that have gathered up from all parts of the world"},{"time":500000,"text":"and ended up in these women."},{"time":502000,"text":"These women have toxic breast milk."},{"time":505000,"text":"They cannot feed their offspring, their children,"},{"time":508000,"text":"their breast milk"},{"time":510000,"text":"because of the accumulation of these toxins"},{"time":512000,"text":"in their food chain,"},{"time":514000,"text":"in their part of the world's"},{"time":516000,"text":"ocean pyramid."},{"time":518000,"text":"That means their immune systems are compromised."},{"time":521000,"text":"It means that their children's development"},{"time":523000,"text":"can be compromised."},{"time":525000,"text":"And the world's attention on this over the last decade"},{"time":528000,"text":"has reduced the problem"},{"time":530000,"text":"for these women,"},{"time":532000,"text":"not by changing the pyramid,"},{"time":534000,"text":"but by changing what they particularly eat out of it."},{"time":536000,"text":"We've taken them out of their natural pyramid"},{"time":538000,"text":"in order to solve this problem."},{"time":541000,"text":"That's a good thing for this particular acute problem,"},{"time":543000,"text":"but it does nothing to solve the pyramid problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"There's other ways of breaking the pyramid."},{"time":548000,"text":"The pyramid, if we jam things in the bottom,"},{"time":551000,"text":"can get backed up like a sewer line that's clogged."},{"time":554000,"text":"And if we jam nutrients, sewage, fertilizer"},{"time":557000,"text":"in the base of that food pyramid,"},{"time":559000,"text":"it can back up all through it."},{"time":561000,"text":"We end up with things we've heard about before:"},{"time":563000,"text":"red tides, for example,"},{"time":565000,"text":"which are blooms of toxic algae"},{"time":567000,"text":"floating through the oceans"},{"time":569000,"text":"causing neurological damage."},{"time":571000,"text":"We can also see blooms of bacteria,"},{"time":573000,"text":"blooms of viruses in the ocean."},{"time":575000,"text":"These are two shots of a red tide coming on shore here"},{"time":578000,"text":"and a bacteria"},{"time":580000,"text":"in the genus vibrio,"},{"time":582000,"text":"which includes the genus that has cholera in it."},{"time":585000,"text":"How many people have seen a \"beach closed\" sign?"},{"time":590000,"text":"Why does that happen?"},{"time":592000,"text":"It happens because we have jammed so much"},{"time":594000,"text":"into the base of the natural ocean pyramid"},{"time":596000,"text":"that these bacteria clog it up"},{"time":598000,"text":"and overfill onto our beaches."},{"time":600000,"text":"Often what jams us up is sewage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603000,"text":"Now how many of you have ever gone to a state park or a national park"},{"time":606000,"text":"where you had a big sign at the front saying,"},{"time":608000,"text":"\"Closed because human sewage"},{"time":610000,"text":"is so far over this park"},{"time":612000,"text":"that you can't use it\"?"},{"time":614000,"text":"Not very often. We wouldn't tolerate that."},{"time":617000,"text":"We wouldn't tolerate our parks"},{"time":619000,"text":"being swamped by human sewage,"},{"time":622000,"text":"but beaches are closed a lot in our country."},{"time":624000,"text":"They're closed more and more and more all around the world for the same reason,"},{"time":627000,"text":"and I believe we shouldn't tolerate that either."},{"time":630000,"text":"It's not just a question of cleanliness;"},{"time":632000,"text":"it's also a question of"},{"time":634000,"text":"how those organisms"},{"time":636000,"text":"then turn into human disease."},{"time":638000,"text":"These vibrios, these bacteria, can actually infect people."},{"time":641000,"text":"They can go into your skin and create skin infections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"This is a graph from NOAA's ocean and human health initiative,"},{"time":647000,"text":"showing the rise of the infections"},{"time":650000,"text":"by vibrio in people"},{"time":653000,"text":"over the last few years."},{"time":655000,"text":"Surfers, for example, know this incredibly."},{"time":658000,"text":"And if you can see on some surfing sites,"},{"time":661000,"text":"in fact, not only do you see"},{"time":663000,"text":"what the waves are like or what the weather's like,"},{"time":665000,"text":"but on some surf rider sites,"},{"time":667000,"text":"you see a little flashing poo alert."},{"time":670000,"text":"That means that the beach might have great waves,"},{"time":673000,"text":"but it's a dangerous place for surfers to be"},{"time":675000,"text":"because they can carry with them,"},{"time":677000,"text":"even after a great day of surfing,"},{"time":679000,"text":"this legacy of an infection that might take a very long time to solve."},{"time":682000,"text":"Some of these infections are actually carrying"},{"time":684000,"text":"antibiotic resistance genes now,"},{"time":686000,"text":"and that makes them even more difficult."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"These same infections"},{"time":690000,"text":"create harmful algal blooms."},{"time":692000,"text":"Those blooms are generating other kinds of chemicals."},{"time":695000,"text":"This is just a simple list of some of the types of poisons"},{"time":698000,"text":"that come out of these harmful algal blooms:"},{"time":700000,"text":"shellfish poisoning,fish ciguatera,"},{"time":703000,"text":"diarrheic shellfish poisoning -- you don't want to know about that --"},{"time":706000,"text":"neurotoxic shellfish poisoning, paralytic shellfish poisoning."},{"time":709000,"text":"These are things that are getting into our food chain"},{"time":711000,"text":"because of these blooms."},{"time":713000,"text":"Rita Calwell very famously"},{"time":715000,"text":"traced a very interesting story"},{"time":717000,"text":"of cholera into human communities,"},{"time":720000,"text":"brought there, not by"},{"time":722000,"text":"a normal human vector,"},{"time":724000,"text":"but by a marine vector, this copepod."},{"time":727000,"text":"Copepods are small crustaceans."},{"time":729000,"text":"They're a tiny fraction of an inch long,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and they can carry on their little legs"},{"time":733000,"text":"some of the cholera bacteria"},{"time":735000,"text":"that then leads to human disease."},{"time":738000,"text":"That has sparked cholera epidemics"},{"time":740000,"text":"in ports along the world"},{"time":742000,"text":"and has led to increased concentration"},{"time":745000,"text":"on trying to make sure shipping"},{"time":747000,"text":"doesn't move these"},{"time":749000,"text":"vectors of cholera around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"So what do you do?"},{"time":753000,"text":"We have major problems in disrupted ecosystem flow"},{"time":756000,"text":"that the pyramid may not be working so well,"},{"time":758000,"text":"that the flow from the base up into it"},{"time":760000,"text":"is being blocked and clogged."},{"time":762000,"text":"What do you do when you have this sort of disrupted flow?"},{"time":765000,"text":"Well, there's a bunch of things you could do."},{"time":768000,"text":"You could call Joe the Plumber, for example."},{"time":770000,"text":"And he could come in"},{"time":772000,"text":"and fix the flow."},{"time":774000,"text":"But in fact, if you look around the world,"},{"time":777000,"text":"not only are there hope spots"},{"time":779000,"text":"for where we may be able to fix problems,"},{"time":781000,"text":"there have been places where problems have been fixed,"},{"time":783000,"text":"where people have come to grips with these issues"},{"time":785000,"text":"and begun to turn them around."},{"time":787000,"text":"Monterey is one of those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789000,"text":"I started out showing how much"},{"time":791000,"text":"we had distressed the Monterey Bay ecosystem"},{"time":794000,"text":"with pollution and the canning industry"},{"time":796000,"text":"and all of the attendant problems."},{"time":798000,"text":"In 1932, that's the picture."},{"time":800000,"text":"In 2009, the picture is dramatically different."},{"time":804000,"text":"The canneries are gone. The pollution has abated."},{"time":807000,"text":"But there's a greater sense here"},{"time":809000,"text":"that what the individual communities need"},{"time":811000,"text":"is working ecosystems."},{"time":813000,"text":"They need a functioning pyramid from the base all the way to the top."},{"time":816000,"text":"And that pyramid"},{"time":818000,"text":"in Monterey, right now,"},{"time":820000,"text":"because of the efforts of a lot of different people,"},{"time":822000,"text":"is functioning better than it's ever functioned"},{"time":824000,"text":"for the last 150 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827000,"text":"It didn't happen accidentally."},{"time":829000,"text":"It happened because many people put their time and effort"},{"time":832000,"text":"and their pioneering spirit into this."},{"time":834000,"text":"On the left there, Julia Platt,"},{"time":836000,"text":"the mayor of my little hometown in Pacific Grove."},{"time":838000,"text":"At 74 years old, became mayor"},{"time":840000,"text":"because something had to be done"},{"time":842000,"text":"to protect the ocean."},{"time":844000,"text":"In 1931, she produced California's first"},{"time":846000,"text":"community-based marine protected area,"},{"time":849000,"text":"right next to the biggest polluting cannery,"},{"time":852000,"text":"because Julia knew"},{"time":854000,"text":"that when the canneries eventually were gone,"},{"time":856000,"text":"the ocean needed a place to grow from,"},{"time":859000,"text":"that the ocean needed a place to spark a seed,"},{"time":862000,"text":"and she wanted to provide that seed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"Other people, like David Packard and Julie Packard,"},{"time":867000,"text":"who were instrumental in producing the Monterey Bay aquarium"},{"time":870000,"text":"to lock into people's notion"},{"time":872000,"text":"that the ocean"},{"time":874000,"text":"and the health of the ocean ecosystem"},{"time":877000,"text":"were just as important to the economy of this area"},{"time":880000,"text":"as eating the ecosystem would be."},{"time":882000,"text":"That change in thinking has led to a dramatic shift,"},{"time":885000,"text":"not only in the fortunes of Monterey Bay,"},{"time":888000,"text":"but other places around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890000,"text":"Well, I want to leave you with the thought that"},{"time":892000,"text":"what we're really trying to do here"},{"time":894000,"text":"is protect this ocean pyramid,"},{"time":896000,"text":"and that ocean pyramid"},{"time":898000,"text":"connects to our own pyramid of life."},{"time":900000,"text":"It's an ocean planet,"},{"time":902000,"text":"and we think of ourselves as a terrestrial species,"},{"time":906000,"text":"but the pyramid of life in the ocean"},{"time":909000,"text":"and our own lives on land"},{"time":911000,"text":"are intricately connected."},{"time":913000,"text":"And it's only through having the ocean being healthy"},{"time":915000,"text":"that we can remain healthy ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}